snippet.title: GOAT LEG FEET | Cooking & Eating in Village | Healthy Goat Leg Recipe | Traditional Mutton Recipes
snippet.description:
For this recipe, we used 100 goat leg feet. Goat legs contain bone, skin, and hair, so we cleaned them with hot water. After cleaning, we boiled the mutton leg feet, and finally, we cooked them with our traditional method. 
Usually, goat leg feet are used for mutton paya or bone soup, but we cook it as gravy. We enjoy this recipe on a rainy evening.

snippet.title: Ibbani Tabbida lleyali Trailer | Vihan, Ankita, Mayuri | Chandrajith Belliappa | Paramvah Studios
snippet.description:
IBBANI TABBIDA ILEYALI is a beautifully crafted musical romance drama that tells the love story of Siddharth and Anahita. Narrated through a palette of colors, visual poetry, and refreshing music, it captures the essence of love through different phases of life and its varying shades. Come, fall in love all over again, and experience the magic of love.

Starring:
Vihan, Ankita Amar, Mayuri Nataraja, Girija Shettar, Salmin Sheriff, Shankar Murthy S.R,  Rakshit Kaup, Davana Dhanraj, Aditya B Pujar,  Anirudh Bhat, Damini Dhanraj

snippet.title: Every Sister Ever | Ft. Tena Jaiin | The Paayal Jain
snippet.description:
Hey Guys
This video shows crazy side of sisters when they are around each other. We love and annoy each other at the same time. It is always Badi Behan vs Choti Behan but it is also Behan Behan ka pyaar. They fight for no reason, sometimes the elder sister wins and vice versa. First child always has to go through family restrictions whereas things are always easier for the younger one , like getting married the pressure of a good idle for younger sister .  Raksha Bandhan celebration with siblings . This is a very comic and relatable video.  Every Behen Shopping fancy rakhi, getting mehendi done girls Favourite Henna, buying new ethnic dress , trying on sharara, anarkali suits, baiting brother for gifts by being sweet, giving him trendy rakhis. Middle class rakshabandhan, school Rakhi celebration and so much more . Every sister ever can relate with this video .
This video is filled with such memories and situations we all have been in. 
Relish and Relive your Childhood Memories.. You will have major nostalgia
Do share it with your friends and family especially mom , sisters , brothers , cousins .. Comment down your Fav Part, 

Happy Raksha Bandhan 2024

paina ke rakhu tez kataar re

 Bas filkar vikar na kariye

Fasgi kit bechari

snippet.title: Tikki Chole Recipe | Crispy Aloo Tikki Chaat | рдХреБрд░рдХреБрд░реА рдЪреЛрд▓реЗ рдЯрд┐рдХреНрдХреА | Chef Sanjyot Keer
snippet.description:
Full written recipe of Tikki Chole
Prep time: 20-25 mins (8-10 hrs soaking)
Cooking time: 1 hour 
Serves: 4-5 people
Chole
Ingredients:
CHICKPEA | рдХрд╛рдмреБрд▓реА рдЪрдиреЗ 250 GRAMS
SALT | рдирдордХ TO TASTE
BLACK CARDAMOM | рдмрдбрд╝реА рдЗрд▓рд╛рдпрдЪреА 1 NO. 
BAY LEAF | рддреЗрдЬ рдкрддреНрддрд╛ 2 NOS. 
CLOVES | рд▓реМрдВрдЧ 4-5 NOS. 
BAKING SODA | рдмреЗрдХрд┐рдВрдЧ рд╕реЛрдбрд╛ A LARGE PINCH
WATER | рдкрд╛рдиреА AS REQUIRED (1 INCH ABOVE CHICKPEAS)
GREEN CHILLI | рд╣рд░реА рдорд┐рд░реНрдЪ 2 NOS. 
GINGER | рдЕрджрд░рдХ 2 INCH
SALT | рдирдордХ A PINCH
GHEE | рдШреА 2 TBSP
CUMIN SEEDS | рдЬреАрд░рд╛ A LARGE PINCH
ASAFOETIDA | рд╣реАрдВрдЧ 1/4 TSP
SALT | рдирдордХ TO TASTE
BLACK SALT | рдХрд╛рд▓рд╛ рдирдордХ 1 TSP
SPICY RED CHILLI POWDER | рддреАрдЦреА рд▓рд╛рд▓ рдорд┐рд░реНрдЪ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ 2 TSP
YELLOW CHILLI POWDER | рдкреАрд▓реА рдорд┐рд░реНрдЪ рдХрд╛ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ 2 TSP
CORIANDER POWDER | рдзрдирд┐рдпрд╛ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ 1 TBSP
GARAM MASALA | рдЧрд░рдо рдорд╕рд╛рд▓рд╛ 1 TSP
TAMARIND | рдЗрдорд▓реА LEMON SIZED BALL (SOAKED)
GINGER | рдЕрджрд░рдХ 1 INCH (JULIENNE)
ROASTED KASURI METHI POWDER | рднреБрдиреА рдХрд╕реВрд░реА рдореЗрдереА рдХрд╛ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ A LARGE PINCH 
FRESH CORIANDER | рд╣рд░рд╛ рдзрдирд┐рдпрд╛ A HANDFUL (CHOPPED)
 Method:
Wash the chickpeas & soak then in water overnight or for 8-10 hours.
Discard the water & add the soaked chickpeas into a pressure cooker along with salt, whole spices, baking soda & water. 
Pressure cooker the chickpeas over high flame for the first whistle then cook for 4-5 more whistles over medium flame. 
Switch off the flame & let the cooker depressurize naturally. 
Make the ginger chilli paste by pounding them using a mortar pestle or a small mixer grinder. 
Set a kadhai over high flame, add the ghee & let it get hot. 
Further add cumin seeds, asafoetida & the paste, stir well & cook over high flame for a minute. 
Add the cooked chickpeas followed by all the powdered spices & tamarind water, stir well & cook over high flame for 7-8 minutes.
Mash a few chickpeas while stirring, this will help the chole to thicken up, the final consistency should be semi-thick but pourable. 
Lastly taste & adjust salt if required & add ginger, kasuri methi & fresh coriander, stir well. 
Your delicious chole are ready. 

Aloo Tikki
Ingredients:
POTATO | рдЖрд▓реВ 7-8 NOS. (BOILED)
SALT | рдирдордХ TO TASTE
CORN FLOUR | рдХреЙрд░реНрди рдлреНрд▓реЛрд░ 3-4 TBSP
CORN FLOUR | рдХреЙрд░реНрди рдлреНрд▓реЛрд░ AS REQUIRED 
GHEE | рдШреА 3 TBSP
Method:
Grate & add the boiled potatoes in a large bowl then add salt & gradually add corn flour.
For the perfect tikki make sure you are using pahadi / indori / chipsona variety of potatoes or else the tikkis wonтАЩt turn out to be crispy. 
Mix well to combine & form a potato dough, the quantity of corn flour might vary depending on the quality of the potatoes, the mixture should not not be sticky it should just bind well. 
Take a small portion from the mixture of about 80-90 grams & from it into a roundel, then slightly press it to form a thick tikki then dust a few pinches of corn flour on it to coat it slightly, shape all the tikkis similarly. 
Set a large, flat pan over high flame & add ghee, let the ghee get moderately hot. 
Place the tikkis & fry them over medium flame until they turn light golden brown from both the sides. 
Then using a potato masher, mash the tikkis to form thick discs then fry the tikkis over medium low flame until they turn golden brown & crisp from both the sides. 
Your super crispy aloo tikkis are ready. 

Green chutney
Ingredients:
MINT | рдкреБрджреАрдирд╛ 1 CUP
FRESH CORIANDER | рд╣рд░рд╛ рдзрдирд┐рдпрд╛ 1 CUP
GINGER | рдЕрджрд░рдХ 1 INCH
GREEN 
CHILLI | рд╣рд░реА рдорд┐рд░реНрдЪ 2 NOS. 
SALT | рдирдордХ TO TASTE
DRY MANGO POWDER | рдЖрдордЪреВрд░ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ 1 TBSP
BLACK SALT | рдХрд╛рд▓рд╛ рдирдордХ ┬╜ TSP
CUMIN POWDER | рдЬреАрд░рд╛ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ ┬╜ TSP
ICE CUBE | рдмрд░реНрдл 
WATER | рдкрд╛рдиреА AS REQUIRED 
Method:
In a mixer jar add all the ingredients of the chutney & grind it into a fine paste, your green chutney is ready.
Amchur Chutney
Ingredients:
DRY MANGO POWDER | рдЖрдордЪреВрд░ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ 75 GRAMS
WATER | рдкрд╛рдиреА 750 ML (ADDED GRADUALLY)
JAGGERY | рдЧреБрдбрд╝ 500 GRAMS
SALT | рдирдордХ TO TASTE
BLACK SALT | рдХрд╛рд▓рд╛ рдирдордХ 1 TSP
ROASTED CUMIN POWDER | рднреБрдиреЗ рдЬреАрд░реЗ рдХрд╛ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ 1 TBSP
GINGER POWDER | рд╕реЛрдВрда 1 TSP
BLACK PEPPER POWDER | рдХрд╛рд▓реА рдорд┐рд░реНрдЪ рдХрд╛ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ ┬╝ TSP
FENNEL POWDER | рд╕реМрдВрдл рдХрд╛ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ ┬╝ TSP
KASHMIRI RED CHILLI POWDER | рдХрд╢реНрдореАрд░реА рд▓рд╛рд▓ рдорд┐рд░реНрдЪ рдкрд╛рдЙрдбрд░ 1 TBSP
Method:
In a stock pot add the dry mango powder & gradually add the water while mixing it continuously to form a lump free mixture. 
Then add all the remaining ingredients & switch on the flame.
Stir well & cook over high flame until the jaggery melts & bring the chutney to a boil. 
Further lower the flame to medium & let it simmer for 15 mins.
Switch off the flame & let it cool down completely.
Amchur ki chutney is ready, you can store it in the fridge for a few months & freeze it to store it for a year.

Mangal Lakshmi unfolds as a poignant narrative, delving into the profound connection shared between two sisters, Mangal and Lakshmi. Set against life's myriad experiences, the story chronicles Mangal's odyssey in search of the ideal match, a 'dulha', for her cherished sibling, Lakshmi. snippet.description:

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.
